			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Raw Pig Skin</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">猪生皮</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Pork Skin; Pork Rinds,猪生皮</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:category level="0">Materials production</common:category>
					<common:category level="1">Food and renewable raw materials</common:category>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<sumFormula>Not Applicable</sumFormula>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Raw pig skin is used in various culinary preparations. It is often bought from local Hispanic markets as it's not typically available in U.S. supermarkets. The skin is soaked in water for at least 6 hours to a day, after which it becomes slightly engorged. It is then placed in a cast iron skillet or heavy pot, covered with rendered fat, and cooked at low heat. Pork rinds, a popular snack, are made from the tough skin layer of pigs that remains after the meat has been removed. The raw skins are salted and dehydrated at low heat for several hours.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">生猪皮可用于各种烹饪。由于在美国超市通常买不到，所以通常从当地的西班牙市场购买。猪皮在水中浸泡至少 6 小时到一天，浸泡后猪皮会略微充血。然后将其放入铸铁平底锅或大锅中，盖上烧焦的油脂，用小火烹制。猪皮是一种很受欢迎的小吃，是用猪去掉肉后剩下的一层坚硬的皮制成的。生皮用盐腌制后在低温下脱水数小时。</common:generalComment>
